$interpreted:
Beast Child: Pray for peace, for peace we pray,
Our shamans dance the night away~

Beast Child: Heaven and earth's incessant spin~
Blessing water, fog and wind!
Tingko: Ah, it's nice to hear that song again!
Jiyanama: Time again for the Peace Ceremony. I wonder who the three tribes will send to serve as shaman?
Tingko: Princess, Your Highness. Please, it's time for lunch.
Tindoiimu: I'm not hungry. Go ahead and eat first.
Jiyanama: Princess, if I may speak plainly, your diet has not been stable recently. If something happened to you, well, we would all be at a loss.
Tingko: Miss Jiyanama, maybe the princess really isn't hungry...
Jiyanama: Tingko, don't you interrupt!
Jiyanama: I am the princess' nanny! I have accompanied her since birth, and must see to it that she's well-cared for.
Jiyanama: If I do not fulfill this sole duty of mine, then my life is meaningless.
Tindoiimu: ...Understood. Fine, I'll eat. I don't wish to cause you trouble, Jiyanama.
Tingko: I don't know what's been going on with ol' Jiya. She's been so cranky recently...
Tindoiimu: You can't blame her. Her son should be turning eleven years old soon.
Tingko: Really? So, he'll attend the Metamorphosis?
Tindoiimu: Yes... she hasn't seen him in nine years, all because of me. Even on his most special day, she's unable to return...
Tingko: Princess, what's the matter with you!?
Jiyanama: I was wondering where Butter went. Madam, you're not keeping it inside you again, are you?
Tindoiimu: I... couldn't help myself...
Jiyanama: Not good. That butterfly is not suited for this environment.
Jiyanama: Keeping it inside will only make you uncomfortable. Put it back in the cage already, will you?
Tingko: Princess, are you feeling any better?
Tindoiimu: Much better. It's just...
Tindoiimu: Being trapped in a cage like that must be so lonely...
Tingko: Not at all. Look how pretty Butter is. Even locked in a cage, it gets plenty of attention.
Tindoiimu: ...I still don't think it's as beautiful as your firefly.
Himawari: Tindoiimu!
Himawari: I'd never expect you to be so petty! I do nothing to provoke you, and yet you go behind my back!
Tindoiimu: Miss Himawari, I don't know what you're talking about.
Himawari: Playing dumb!? Seriously!?
Himawari: It was decided long ago that I would serve as wind shaman for the Peace Ceremony.
Himawari: You must have been speaking ill of me to Juan Yun, otherwise why would he suddenly change his mind!?
Tingko: The shamans should be one from each sect. Why would he pick our princess?
Jiyanama: Miss Himawari, there must be some misunderstanding...
Himawari: I am speaking to your princess!
Himawari: I usually show respect, as you are princess of the Insect Tribe, but do not think that I fear you.
Himawari: Must I remind you who it was that begged us for forgiveness?
Tindoiimu: .........
Himawari: You know exactly what I'm talking about.
Himawari: A political hostage should act accordingly. Behave as you ought to.
Himawari: Before trying to take what isn't rightfully yours, first ask yourself whether or not you deserve it.
Tingko: The princess was absolutely unaware of this. I would not lie to you. Miss Himawari, please go ask Lord Juan Yun himself!
Himawari: Well then. You dare question me, as well as insult Lord Juan Yun!?
Himawari: You dirty little bug...
Tingko: I wouldn't dare! I just think you've misunderstood Princess Tindoiimu...
Tindoiimu: Tingko, enough. You may leave.
Tingko: But we really didn't recommend you to Lord Juan Yun, princess!
Tingko: Regardless, at least you're the true heir to the Insect Tribe. Himawari may have been taken in by the Wind Sect,
Tingko: but she was still born into the Leopard Tribe, part of the Fog Sect. She has just as little of a right to be wind shaman as you do!
Tindoiimu: Tingko!
Himawari: Impudence!
Tingko: Ah!
Himawari: It appears... that your princess has not taught her subordinates how to speak properly. I shall do it for her...
Himawari: First, I shall tear open that eloquent mouth of yours!
Himawari: You!?
Himawari: (Eeesh, didn't expect her grip to be so strong...)
Himawari: ...Get off!
Tindoiimu: ......
Qilin Bodyguard : Did you not hear her? Let the lady go!
Himawari: Y-You...
Himawari: You think you'll get away with this?
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: I did not do well teaching my subordinates. Forgive me for upsetting you, Miss Himawari.
Tindoiimu: I'm afraid your hand has been injured. I shall pay the price myself.
Jiyanama: Eeeee! Blood!
Himawari: You...
Tindoiimu: If you are still not satisfied, I will cut deeper...
Himawari: E... Enough!
Himawari: Hmph. For the time being, it appears you are sincere.
Himawari: But don't let this happen again, or next time I won't be so forgiving.
Tindoiimu: Tingko, are you alright?
Tingko: It's fine...
Tingko: ...Princess, you really do care about me...
Tingko: Ah! Butter!
Tindoiimu: I got it!
Tindoiimu: Trying to get away again, are we?
Tindoiimu: You know you can't hide that natural beauty.
Tindoiimu: The future King of the Insect Tribe has already picked you to stay by his side.
???: Yes, natural beauty... natural beauty, indeed.
